main event: A civilian in Reseda, California reported observing a bright sphere-like light surrounded by an elliptical light, with the sphere being approximately five times brighter than the outer light.
interesting points: The observation was made on the ground without the aid of any mechanical equipment.
The core of the sphere was bright golden in color, and no discernible details were visible.
The object was observed at approximately 60 degrees above the horizon, made very little movement, and disappeared like turning off a light.
The observer estimated observing the object for approximately two minutes.
There were no reports on UFO made as a matter of routine procedure, and no shape, size, or color of the object was reported.
sighted object: bright sphere-like light surrounded by an elliptical light
photographs: no photographs provided in the report
